{
  "contentionNodeId": "mnode-1",
  "nodes": [
    {
      "id": "mnode-1",
      "kind": "main-conclusion",
      "text": "Humans should not be allowed to pet dogs without obtaining explicit permission from the dog.",
      "role": "Moderator",
      "round": 1,
      "confidence": 1,
      "createdAt": 1777742948791
    },
    {
      "id": "mnode-2",
      "kind": "premise",
      "text": "Petting a dog without its explicit permission can cause stress or fear in the animal, compromising its welfare.",
      "role": "Advocate",
      "round": 1,
      "confidence": 1,
      "createdAt": 1777742949724
    },
    {
      "id": "mnode-3",
      "kind": "objection",
      "text": "Some dogs may enjoy being petted by humans even without explicit permission, so assuming harm in all cases is overgeneralized.",
      "role": "Critic",
      "round": 1,
      "confidence": 1,
      "createdAt": 1777742952010
    },
    {
      "id": "mnode-4",
      "kind": "objection",
      "text": "There is insufficient empirical evidence provided to substantiate the claim that some dogs enjoy being petted without explicit permission.",
      "role": "Auditor",
      "round": 1,
      "confidence": 1,
      "createdAt": 1777742953792
    },
    {
      "id": "mnode-5",
      "kind": "rebuttal",
      "text": "Even if some dogs enjoy unsolicited petting, the inability to reliably distinguish these cases justifies a general rule requiring explicit permission to protect animal welfare.",
      "role": "Sophist",
      "round": 1,
      "confidence": 1,
      "createdAt": 1777742954878
    },
    {
      "id": "mnode-6",
      "kind": "premise",
      "text": "Respecting a dog's autonomy by seeking explicit permission aligns with ethical principles of consent and reduces the risk of negative interactions.",
      "role": "Advocate",
      "round": 2,
      "confidence": 1,
      "createdAt": 1777742956284
    },
    {
      "id": "mnode-7",
      "kind": "objection",
      "text": "The concept of obtaining explicit permission from a dog is ambiguous and not practically achievable, undermining the feasibility of the main conclusion.",
      "role": "Critic",
      "round": 2,
      "confidence": 1,
      "createdAt": 1777742957905
    },
    {
      "id": "mnode-8",
      "kind": "rebuttal",
      "text": "Guidelines for interpreting canine body language can provide a practical framework for determining when a dog may be giving permission to be petted.",
      "role": "Sophist",
      "round": 2,
      "confidence": 1,
      "createdAt": 1777742959575
    },
    {
      "id": "mnode-9",
      "kind": "objection",
      "text": "There is a lack of empirical validation demonstrating that guidelines for interpreting canine body language are consistently reliable across different dogs and contexts.",
      "role": "Auditor",
      "round": 2,
      "confidence": 1,
      "createdAt": 1777742961840
    }
  ],
